        flow:fileSizeMB 2.07e+01 ;
        flow:namespace "Python_101_20251107T095608Z_fdc0dc" ;
        flow:uploadTimestamp "2025-11-07T09:56:08.389866+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
        dcterms:description "Python 101 2nd Edition, authored by Michael Driscoll and published on Leanpub on 29 August 2020, is a beginner‑to‑intermediate guide that introduces the Python programming language and its ecosystem. Structured into four main parts—The Basics, Intermediate Materials, Tutorials, and Python Packaging and Distribution—the book walks readers through fundamental concepts, practical coding techniques, and the steps needed to package and share Python projects. Early chapters cover installation across major platforms (Windows, macOS, Linux, Android/iOS), ensuring readers can set up a working environment regardless of their operating system. The text also includes sections on target audience, author background, conventions, and system requirements, as well as supplemental resources such as source code, reader feedback mechanisms, and an errata list. Technical reviewers Ethan Furman and Martin Breuss contributed to the manuscript’s accuracy. Designed for newcomers and those seeking to solidify their Python knowledge, the resource combines clear explanations with hands‑on examples, aiming to help readers progress from initial setup to creating and distributing their own Python applications." ;
        dcterms:title "Python 101.pdf" .

